cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with image analysis and topology, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.GR (Graphics). The use of discrete Morse theory and persistent homology suggests that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper introduces software for predicting future image properties, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
